it.unimi.di.law.bubing.util

Class LockFreeQueue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unimi.di.law.bubing.util.LockFreeQueue<T>

  • public class LockFreeQueue<T>
extends Object
    A thin layer around a ConcurrentLinkedQueue that exhibits a subset of the available methods, and keeps track in an AtomicLong of the size of the queue, so that size() can return in constant time.
    Author:
    Sebastiano Vigna

      • size

        public long size()
        Returns the (approximate) size of this queue.

        This methods returns in constant time (it is just an AtomicLong.get()). Due to concurrent modifications, the returned value might not reflect the actual number of elements in the queue.

        Returns:
        the (approximate) size of this queue.
